description.div: The Silom Christian Cemetery is a Christian Chinese cemetery in direct vicinity to the Hakka, Hokkien and Cantonese Cemeteries. To enter the cemetery one has to enter the alley to the Cantonese school and push a rolling gate open, which is unlocked during day time. A gardien is living insight the area of the Christian and Paris Cemetery and he will lock and unlock the cemetery. Within the compound, the cemetery is separated by a fence in two parts, the Christian Cemetery and the Parise Cemetery.
